If the segments joining the points A(a,b) and B(c,d) subtends an angle \theta, at the origin, then what will be the \theta.
Create a textbox.
text:If the segments joining the points A and B subtends an angle \theta at the origin, find the angle \cos(\theta)
A=(a,b)
B=(c,d)
O=(0,0)
l=Segment(O,A)
m=Segment(O,B)
n=Segment(A,B)
AOB=\theta
l^2=a^2+b^2
m^2=c^2+d^2
n^2=(c-a)^2+(d-b)^2
f=a*c+b*d
Text box: k=\dfrac{f}{l*m}
Use cosine formula for triangle OAB, \cos{\theta}=k
Create a text box to show the angle cos(\theta).
https://www.geogebra.org/m/sn3jsuzt
